# 🔐 Cybersecurity Task 1 - Vulnerability Assessment Report

## 🌐 Target Website
OWASP Juice Shop (Intentionally vulnerable web application)

---

## 🎯 Objective
To perform a passive vulnerability assessment and identify security issues using standard security tools.

---

## 🛠 Tools Used
- Browser Developer Tools
- OWASP ZAP (Passive Scan)
- Nmap (Network Scan)

---

## 🔍 Findings

### 1. Exposed Services
- Open ports detected: 21 (FTP), 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS)
- Server information exposed (Heroku)
- Internal endpoint references visible

### 2. Security Header Issues
- Missing Content-Security-Policy (CSP)
- Missing Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS)
- Open CORS policy (`*`)

### 3. Network Exposure
- Open ports identified using Nmap scan

---

## ⚠️ Risk Summary
- Medium: Security header misconfiguration
- Medium: Network exposure
- Low: Information disclosure

---

## 🔧 Recommendations
- Implement CSP and HSTS headers
- Restrict CORS policy to trusted domains
- Disable unnecessary services like FTP

---

## 📌 Conclusion
The application contains multiple security misconfigurations that increase the attack surface. No active exploitation was performed; only passive analysis was done.

